From source 0, shortest distance to 1 is -5.

Thatâ€™s negative, but no negative cycle exists.

The real criterion for a negative cycle is:
ðŸ‘‰ Even after V-1 relaxations, some edge can still be relaxed.
That indicates distances can keep decreasing infinitely â†’ negative cycle.

------------------------------------------
Note:- Dijktra's Algorithm will fail, if it has negative cycles.
and negative cycles may come from negative edges. thats why we use the bellman ford algorithm. 

class Solution {
    public int[] bellmanFord(int V, int[][] err, int src) {
        int[]res=new int[V];
        Arrays.fill(res,(int)(Math.pow(10,8)));
        res[src]=0;
        for(int i=0;i<V;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<err.length;j++){
                int s=err[j][0];
                int d=err[j][1];
                int w=err[j][2];
                if(res[s]!=(int)(Math.pow(10,8)) && res[s]+w<res[d]){
                    // if it has reached the vthe position and still relaxing then the negative cycle exits
                    if(i==V-1){
                        return new int[]{-1};
                    }
                    res[d]=res[s]+w;
                }
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
